FBIS3-11472 "drlat055_m_94004" FBIS-LAT-94-055 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Mar 1994 Brazil U.S. To Provide Security for Gaviria if Elected OAS Secretary General PY2103180594 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO in Portuguese 19 Mar 94 Section 5 p 11 PY2103180594 Sao Paulo FOLHA DE SAO PAULO Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [From the Joyce Pascowitch social column] [Text] When he assumes as the new OAS general secretary, [Colombian President] Cesar Gaviria Trujillo will be able to relax, knowing he is protected from the Colombian drug cartels. Once he assumes the post he will be provided the security to which all OAS general secretaries are entitled, but this time supplied by the U.S. Government.
